column11:
Due to a customer availability issue, we held our monthly review meeting in person at Cambridge the week prior to our normally scheduled meeting. We were able to discuss the full month, challenges and achievements, as well as upcoming plans and projects, and we have another follow up meeting on 3/10/2026 where any additional items not yet available at the time of the original review can be discussed.

At the review on 2/26, we discussed:
- Feedback from the previous month of VIP trips around Sanofi locations;
- Amendments to the contract covering 2025 changes (executed) as well as 2026 changes (in review);
- Growth opportunities at Toronto, Swiftwater, and Orlando;
- Challenges CB is facing at Waltham with their customer, and how SBM can continue to support them through partnership and inclusion in any and all communication;
- Some CB account leadership changes, where Rick now reports directly to Lani Wild rather than to Jason Goddard who sits in London;
- Quality successes at Framingham
- Aligning on Morristown and Cambridge expectations and assuring that SBM's expansions with new floors are not causing CBRE to miss their budget targets;
- Success of the Safety communication reset that we did at the end of January/beginning of February;
